                                                                                                                                          The largest hoard of Anglo-Saxon gold, consisting of about 1,500 items and dating back to between 675AD and 725AD, has been found by an unemployed 55-year-old man pottering around on a farm in Staffordshire with a 14-year-old metal detector.                 The grandson of Chairman Mao has been promoted to become the youngest major-general in the Peoples Liberation Army.                   An experimental AIDS vaccine made from two older versions has made major progress in finding an effective way to combat the illness, researchers said today.                             Museum officials hold a strip of gold with a Biblical inscription. (AP)
                                                                                                                                                                        
